         <!-- HERE STARTS THE PROSE DESCRIPTION OF THIS CUSTOMISATION -->
         <head>A TEI Customization to encode Paul Rémond's letters</head>

         <p>The project is based on the study and organization of the correspondence of Paul Rémond,
            Bishop of Nice from 1930 to 1963.</p>

         <p>Ordained a priest in 1899 in Besançon, Paul Rémond quickly embarked on a brilliant
            ecclesiastical career, notably as a preacher. Drafted during World War I, he ended the
            war as the highest-ranking cleric in the French army. In 1921, he was consecrated a
            bishop to oversee the newly established chaplaincy of the Army of the Rhine, created by
            the government to help improve acceptance of the occupation among German Catholic
            populations.</p>

         <p>In 1930, at the end of the Occupation, Paul Rémond accepted the See of Nice, where he
            remained until his death. He was a republican and patriotic bishop. He organized
            triumphalist religious celebrations that attracted tens of thousands of people. He
            developed Catholic Action, unionism, and clergy training.</p>

         <p>He condemned Nazi anti-Semitism as early as April 1933. Appalled by the Italian and
            German occupations as well as by collaboration and state anti-Semitism, he devoted
            himself to supporting the Resistance. With a Jewish friend, he established a network at
            the bishopric that hid and saved 527 Jewish children. His funeral, on April 27, 1963, in
            central Nice, was a grand ceremony that made his popularity and prestige evident.</p>

         <p>His correspondence provides a rich and varied account of his actions. Through his
            writings, we gain insight into his spiritual reflections, his decisions as a religious
            authority, and his interactions with other institutions of the time, making it a
            valuable source for understanding the historical and ecclesiastical context of this
            period.</p>

         <p>The encoding adheres to the TEI (Text Encoding Initiative) standard, a robust and widely
            accepted framework for encoding textual materials, particularly historical documents. By
            encoding these letters, the project aims to preserve the cultural and historical value
            of the correspondence while enabling a variety of academic and practical
            applications.</p>

         <p>Potential applications include: <list>
               <item>Digital Archiving: Facilitating the long-term preservation and accessibility of
                  the letters in digital repositories.</item>
               <item>Scholarly Research: Supporting historians, linguists, and theologians in their
                  analysis of the language, context, and content of the letters.</item>
               <item>Textual Analysis: Enabling computational techniques such as text mining,
                  semantic analysis, and network mapping of relationships between people, places,
                  and organizations.</item>
               <item>Educational Use: Providing a valuable resource for teaching students about
                  historical correspondence, church history, and encoding standards.</item>
               <item>Public Engagement: Allowing museums, archives, and cultural organizations to
                  create interactive exhibitions or digital resources accessible to a broader
                  audience.</item>
            </list> The encoding approach focuses on balancing historical fidelity with
            extensibility to ensure the data can be used and enhanced over time. Key decisions
            regarding the use of elements and attributes are outlined below.</p>

         <p>The following TEI ODD defines a TEI customization to encode Paul Rémond's letters. It
            includes the five elements from the header module: <list rend="numbered">
               <item>
                  <gi>teiHeader</gi> from the "header" module to store required metadata</item>
               <item>
                  <gi>fileDesc</gi> from the "header" module to record information about this
                  file</item>
               <item>
                  <gi>titleStmt</gi> from the "header" module to record information about the
                  title</item>
               <item>
                  <gi>publicationStmt</gi> from the "header" module to detail how it is
                  published</item>
               <item>
                  <gi>sourceDesc</gi> from the "header" module to record where it is from</item>
            </list> The "core" module allows to structure the encoding of letters by allowing the
            markup of paragraphs (<gi>p</gi>) and lines break (<gi>lb</gi>) among other information
            while the "textstructure" module allows to encode each letter in a different
               <gi>div</gi> and to structure each letter with a <gi>opener</gi> and a
               <gi>closer</gi> even structured. It also includes many "namesdate" elements to index
            names of people, places and organizations. The list of named entities is encoded and
            referenced with identifiers in the <gi>back</gi>.</p>

         <!-- HERE STARTS CUSTOMISATION -->
         <schemaSpec ident="oddforpaulremond" start="TEI ">
            <desc>A customisation to encode Paul Rémond's letters.</desc>
            <moduleRef key="tei"/>
            <!--Checking module textcrit-->
            <classRef key="att.textCritical"/>
            <classRef key="model.rdgLike"/>
            <classRef key="model.rdgPart"/>
            <classSpec ident="att.textCritical" type="atts" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="type" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="cause" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="varSeq" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="require" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </classSpec>
            <!--Checking module msdescription-->
            <classRef key="model.physDescPart"/>
            <moduleRef key="msdescription" include="msDesc msIdentifier repository"/>
            <elementSpec ident="msDesc" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="corresp" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="type" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </elementSpec>
            <elementSpec ident="msIdentifier" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="corresp" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </elementSpec>
            <elementSpec ident="repository" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="corresp" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="key" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="ref" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </elementSpec>
            <!--Checking module namesdates-->
            <classRef key="model.persNamePart"/>
            <moduleRef key="namesdates"
               include="orgName persName surname forename roleName placeName country settlement birth death listOrg listPerson listPlace org person place"/>
            <elementSpec ident="orgName" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="calendar" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="corresp" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="when" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="key" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="type" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </elementSpec>
            <elementSpec ident="persName" mode="change">
               <desc>In the text content of letters, the <gi>persName</gi> element encodes a
                  person’s name or a reference to a person while in Back Matter, this element is
                  contain inside a <gi>person</gi> element.</desc>
               <constraintSpec ident="persName_child_of_person" mode="change" scheme="isoschematron">
                  <desc>The <gi>persName</gi> element inside <gi>person</gi> must have exactly one
                        <gi>forename</gi>, <gi>surname</gi>, and <gi>roleName</gi>.</desc>
                  <constraint>
                     <sch:rule context="tei:person/tei:persName">
                        <sch:assert
                           test="count(tei:forename) = 1 and count(tei:surname) = 1 and count(tei:roleName) = 1"
                           > The persName element inside person must have exactly one forename,
                           surname, and roleName. </sch:assert>
                     </sch:rule>
                     <sch:rule context="tei:p/tei:persName">
                        <sch:assert test="@ref">The persName element in the correspondence textual
                           content must have a @ref attribute</sch:assert>
                     </sch:rule>
                  </constraint>
               </constraintSpec>
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="calendar" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="corresp" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="when" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="key" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="type" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </elementSpec>
            <elementSpec ident="surname" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="corresp" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="key" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="ref" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="type" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </elementSpec>
            <elementSpec ident="forename" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="corresp" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="key" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="ref" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="type" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </elementSpec>
            <elementSpec ident="roleName" mode="change">
               <desc>The <gi>roleName</gi> element specifies the person’s role</desc>
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="corresp" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="key" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="ref" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="type" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </elementSpec>
            <elementSpec ident="placeName" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="calendar" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="when" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="corresp" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="key" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="type" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </elementSpec>
            <elementSpec ident="country" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="calendar" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="corresp" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="type" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="when" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </elementSpec>
            <elementSpec ident="settlement" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="calendar" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="corresp" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="key" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="type" mode="change">
                     <valList mode="add" type="closed">
                        <valItem ident="city"/>
                     </valList>
                  </attDef>
                  <attDef ident="when" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </elementSpec>
            <elementSpec ident="birth" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="calendar" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="type" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="corresp" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="when" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="key" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="ref" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="type" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </elementSpec>
            <elementSpec ident="death" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="calendar" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="type" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="when" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="corresp" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="key" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="ref" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="type" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </elementSpec>
            <elementSpec ident="listOrg" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="corresp" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="type" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </elementSpec>
            <elementSpec ident="listPerson" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="corresp" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="type" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </elementSpec>
            <elementSpec ident="listPlace" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="corresp" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="type" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </elementSpec>
            <elementSpec ident="org" mode="change">
               <desc>The <gi>org</gi> encodes an organization referenced in the correspondence. This
                  element as two children : <gi>orgName</gi> (name of the organization) and
                     <gi>desc</gi> (organization’s nature or purpose).</desc>
               <content>
                  <sequence>
                     <elementRef key="orgName"/>
                     <elementRef key="desc"/>
                  </sequence>
               </content>
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="xml:id" mode="change">
                     <desc>The <att>xml:id</att> attribute provides a unique identifier for
                        reference throughout the document.</desc>
                  </attDef>
                  <attDef ident="role" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="corresp" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="type" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
               <exemplum>
                  <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
                     <org xml:id="org_dominican_order">
                        <orgName>Ordre des Dominicains</orgName>
                        <desc>Ordre religieux catholique fondé par Dominique de Guzman</desc>
                     </org>
                  </egXML>
               </exemplum>
            </elementSpec>
            <elementSpec ident="person" mode="change">
               <desc>The <gi>person</gi> element represents an individual person. In our project
                     <gi>person</gi> must contain a sequence of three elements: <gi>persName</gi>
                  <gi>birth</gi>and <gi>death</gi> as children. No other elements ara
                  allowed.</desc>
               <content>
                  <sequence>
                     <elementRef key="persName"/>
                     <elementRef key="birth"/>
                     <elementRef key="death"/>
                  </sequence>
               </content>
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="xml:id" mode="change">
                     <desc>The <att>xml:id</att> attribute provides a unique identifier for
                        reference throughout the document.</desc>
                  </attDef>
                  <attDef ident="role" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="sex" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="gender" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="age" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="corresp" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
               <exemplum>
                  <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
                     <person xml:id="person_paul_remond">
                        <persName>
                           <forename>Paul</forename>
                           <surname>Rémond</surname>
                           <roleName>Évêque de Nice</roleName>
                        </persName>
                        <birth>
                           <date>1873</date>
                        </birth>
                        <death>
                           <date>1963</date>
                        </death>
                     </person>
                  </egXML>
               </exemplum>
               <exemplum>
                  <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
                     <person xml:id="person_pie_xi">
                        <persName>
                           <forename>Achille</forename>
                           <surname>Ratti</surname>
                           <roleName>Pape (sous le nom de Pie XI, 1922-1939)</roleName>
                        </persName>
                        <birth>
                           <date>1857</date>
                        </birth>
                        <death>
                           <date>1939</date>
                        </death>
                     </person>
                  </egXML>
               </exemplum>
            </elementSpec>
            <elementSpec ident="place" mode="change">
               <desc>The <gi>place</gi> element represents an individual place.</desc>
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="corresp" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="type" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
               <exemplum>
                  <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
                     <place xml:id="place_nice">
                        <placeName>Nice</placeName>
                     </place>
                  </egXML>
               </exemplum>
            </elementSpec>
            <!--Checking module dictionaries-->
            <classRef key="att.lexicographic"/>
            <classRef key="model.entryLike"/>
            <classRef key="model.formPart"/>
            <classRef key="model.gramPart"/>
            <classRef key="model.lexicalRefinement"/>
            <classRef key="model.morphLike"/>
            <classRef key="model.ptrLike.form"/>
            <classSpec ident="att.lexicographic" type="atts" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="expand" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="split" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="value" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="location" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="mergedIn" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="opt" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </classSpec>
            <!--Checking module tagdocs-->
            <classRef key="att.combinable"/>
            <classRef key="att.identified"/>
            <classRef key="model.contentPart"/>
            <classSpec ident="att.combinable" type="atts" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="mode" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </classSpec>
            <classSpec ident="att.identified" type="atts" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="ident" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="predeclare" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="module" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </classSpec>
            <classSpec ident="att.ascribed.directed" type="atts" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="toWhom" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </classSpec>
            <classSpec ident="att.dimensions" type="atts" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="unit" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="quantity" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="extent" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="precision" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="scope" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </classSpec>
            <classSpec ident="att.damaged" type="atts" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="agent" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="degree" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="group" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </classSpec>
            <classSpec ident="att.datable.w3c" type="atts" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="notBefore" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="notAfter" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="from" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="to" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </classSpec>
            <classSpec ident="att.datable" type="atts" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="period" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </classSpec>
            <classSpec ident="att.divLike" type="atts" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="org" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="sample" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </classSpec>
            <classSpec ident="att.media" type="atts" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="width" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="height" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="scale" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </classSpec>
            <classSpec ident="att.naming" type="atts" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="role" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="nymRef" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </classSpec>
            <classSpec ident="att.typed" type="atts" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="subtype" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </classSpec>
            <classSpec ident="att.pointing" type="atts" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="targetLang" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="evaluate" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </classSpec>
            <classSpec ident="att.pointing.group" type="atts" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="domains" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="targFunc" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </classSpec>
            <classSpec ident="att.segLike" type="atts" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="function" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </classSpec>
            <classSpec ident="att.timed" type="atts" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="start" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="end" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </classSpec>
            <classSpec ident="att.transcriptional" type="atts" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="status" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="cause" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="seq" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </classSpec>
            <classSpec ident="att.personal" type="atts" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="full" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="sort" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </classSpec>
            <!--Checking module core-->
            <moduleRef key="core"
               include="p hi desc name address street num date abbr expan ref list item head pb lb title"/>
            <elementSpec ident="p" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="corresp" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </elementSpec>
            <elementSpec ident="hi" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="corresp" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </elementSpec>
            <elementSpec ident="desc" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="type" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="corresp" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="type" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </elementSpec>
            <elementSpec ident="name" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="calendar" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="corresp" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="key" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="ref" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="when" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="type" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </elementSpec>
            <elementSpec ident="address" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="corresp" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </elementSpec>
            <elementSpec ident="street" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="corresp" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </elementSpec>
            <elementSpec ident="num" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="type" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="value" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="corresp" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="type" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </elementSpec>
            <elementSpec ident="date" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="corresp" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="key" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="ref" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="type" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </elementSpec>
            <elementSpec ident="abbr" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="type" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="corresp" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="type" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </elementSpec>
            <elementSpec ident="expan" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="corresp" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </elementSpec>
            <elementSpec ident="ref" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="corresp" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="type" mode="change">
                     <valList mode="add" type="closed">
                        <valItem ident="prev"/>
                     </valList>
                  </attDef>
               </attList>
            </elementSpec>
            <elementSpec ident="list" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="type" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="corresp" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="type" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </elementSpec>
            <elementSpec ident="item" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="corresp" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </elementSpec>
            <elementSpec ident="head" mode="change">
               <desc>In our project, <gi>head</gi> a brief summary of the letter's content,
                  improving accessibility for researchers.</desc>
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="corresp" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="type" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </elementSpec>
            <elementSpec ident="pb" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="corresp" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="type" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </elementSpec>
            <elementSpec ident="lb" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="corresp" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="type" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </elementSpec>
            <elementSpec ident="title" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="calendar" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="level" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="type" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="corresp" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="type" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="key" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="ref" mode="delete"/>
                  <attDef ident="when" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </elementSpec>
            <!--Checking module header-->
            <moduleRef key="header"
               include="teiHeader fileDesc titleStmt publicationStmt authority idno availability licence sourceDesc profileDesc textClass keywords correspDesc correspAction correspContext"/>
            <elementSpec ident="teiHeader" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="corresp" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </elementSpec>
            <elementSpec ident="fileDesc" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="corresp" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </elementSpec>
            <elementSpec ident="titleStmt" mode="change">
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="corresp" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
            </elementSpec>
            <elementSpec ident="publicationStmt" mode="change">
               <desc>In our project <gi>publicationStmt</gi> must contain a sequence of two
                  elements: <gi>authority</gi> and <gi>availability</gi> as children. No other
                  elements ara allowed.</desc>
               <content>
                  <sequence>
                     <elementRef key="authority" minOccurs="1" maxOccurs="1"/>
                     <elementRef key="availability" minOccurs="1" maxOccurs="1"/>
                  </sequence>
               </content>
               <attList>
                  <attDef ident="corresp" mode="delete"/>
               </attList>
               <exemplum>
                  <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
                     <publicationStmt>
                        <authority>Amélie Dogan</authority>
                        <availability status="free">
